To set up an Amplify AppSync API with Apollo Client, you can follow these high-level steps:

1. Set up your Amplify project: First, you'll need to create an Amplify project and add the AppSync API to your project. This can be done using the Amplify CLI or the Amplify Console.
2. Create your schema and resolvers: Next, you can define your schema and resolvers for your AppSync API using the Amplify CLI or the Amplify Console. This will involve defining your GraphQL schema and implementing your resolvers for each data source (e.g. DynamoDB, Lambda, etc.).
3. Install the Apollo Client library: With your AppSync API set up, you can install the `@apollo/client` library in your app using NPM or Yarn:


```java
npm install @apollo/client
```
4. Configure Apollo Client: With the `@apollo/client` library installed, you can configure it to use your AppSync API. This involves creating an instance of the `ApolloClient` class and passing in your AppSync endpoint URL and authorization headers:


```javascript
