2. Limits: In Apex, limits are the constraints placed on the number of resources that can be used by a single transaction. Limits are designed to prevent a single transaction from consuming too many resources and affecting the performance of the system as a whole. Some common governor limits include the number of database queries that can be executed, the number of CPU time that can be used, and the number of records that can be processed.

In Apex, you can check the current limit values and remaining limit values using the `Limits` class. For example, you can check the remaining number of database queries using the following code:


```less
System.debug(Limits.getQueries());
