 global Database.QueryLocator start(Database.BatchableContext bc) {
 // Code to define the start of the batch process
 return Database.getQueryLocator('SELECT Id FROM Account');
 }

 global void execute(Database.BatchableContext bc, List<sObject> scope) {
 // Code to process each batch of records
 List<Account> accounts = (List<Account>)scope;
 // Update the records
 update accounts;
 }

 global void finish(Database.BatchableContext bc) {
 // Code to run after all batches are processed
 }
}
```
In this example, the `BatchApexExample` class implements the `Database.Batchable` interface, and defines the `start`, `execute`, and `finish` methods. The `start` method is used to define the start of the batch process and return a `Database.QueryLocator` that specifies the records to be processed. The `execute` method is used to process each batch of records, and the `finish` method is used to run code after all batches are processed. The batch process can be started by calling the `Database.executeBatch` method and passing an instance of the `BatchApexExample` class as an argument.

